commit.message: CI: Start using new C-API functions in CPython 3.13 (also in Limited API).
CI: Test Limited C-API functions in CPython 3.13.
Fix variable usage and add comment for error case.
Avoid defining our own redundant helper function if we can use the one from CPython directly.
Make PY_HEX_VERSION check for Py3.13 easier to read: "0x030D0000" looks a lot like "0x03000000", whereas "0x030d0000" is easier to distinguish.

Remove usages of private CPython C-API functions that disappeared in CPython 3.13.

See https://github.com/python/cpython/issues/106320
CI: Install latest pip and setuptools in Py3.11+ (also since distutils is gone in Py3.13).
Disable _PyLong_AsByteArray() usage in Py3.13. It was removed in 3.13a1.

Fix version guard: Py3.13, not Py3.11.
Also fix a test output check in Py3.13+: the error message starts with a capital letter in CPython.

Work around a change in CPython 3.13a1 that prevents calling PyList_SET_ITEM() in a valid use case.

See https://github.com/python/cpython/issues/106168

Refactor the optimised PyUnicode_ConcatInPlace() code to clarify the reference counting of the result and to make sure we only resize and copy into strings to which we own the only reference.
Background is that PyUnicode_CopyCharacters() gained an additional check in Py3.13a1 that conflicts with our previous safety net of early incref-ing the resized string.

See https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/5767#issuecomment-1783298441
Make __Pyx_PyBytes_Join() work in Python 3.13 where _PyBytes_Join() is gone.
Do not install any test dependencies in Python 3.13 for now since they fail to build.

title: Adapt to C-API changes in CPython 3.13
